Social relations are disrupted. Individuals are staying at home. Wearing masks is becoming more and more common in some countries where people were not used to it, and individuals no longer see each other's facial expressions. The COVID-19 pandemic is having a psychological impact on individuals (
 Asmundson and Taylor, 2020; 
 Li et al., 2020). For adolescents with psychiatric disorders, lockdown may result in a sudden break or shift in care.
